{{wikipedia}}
==English==
===Etymology===
From Old English '''[[Englisc]]''', from '''[[Engle]]''' ("the [[Angles]]," a Germanic tribe).

===Pronunciation===
*ĭng'glĭsh
*{{IPA|/ˈɪŋglɪʃ/}}
*{{SAMPA|/"INglIS/}}

===Noun===
'''English''' (''plural:'' '''Englishes''')

# A [[language]] originating in [[w:England|England]], but now spoken in all parts of the [[British Isles]]. Also spoken in the [[United States of America]], [[Australia]], [[New Zealand]], [[Canada]], [[Ireland]], [[Jamaica]], [[Bermuda]], and as a second language in many other countries.

